String Class:
   String class is designed to store symbols(letters(A,d,C), numbers(10,25),special characters
   (#,$,%), in the form of a group. There are many methods already written by java developers
   that we can just use. String class is the most widely used class in java.
   -for example:
    length()
    startsWith()
    endsWith()
    contains()
Why we should learn about this class.
    1) Very important for coding questions.
    2) Most widely used class in all java.
    3) Most of the information in real lefe is present in the form of String.





Note:
    Very important for coding questions.
    1) If else
    2) Loops
    3) Arrays
    4) Strings
